<p style="text-align:left;font-size:20px;font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;">About Eastern University (EU)</p>

<p>Eastern University was established in 2003 under the Private University Act 1992, as amended in 1998. It is approved by the Ministry of Education, Government of Bangladesh and by the University Grants Commission (UGC). The University was set up by Eastern University Foundation - a non-profit, non-political and philanthropic organization. Its founders include academics, chartered accountants, engineers, industrialists and retired civil servants. At present, the Foundation has 30 members. The governance of Eastern University is carried out as per the Private Universities Act of 2010 by several bodies: Board of Governors, Syndicate, Academic Council, Curriculum Committee, Finance Committee, Teacher Selection Committee and Disciplinary Committee. 
    </p>
<p>The vision of Eastern University is to become a leading University in South Asia in its chosen fields of higher education. Its mission is to be a "Center of Excellence" by setting a new standard of quality teaching and quality education in Bangladesh, keeping the challenges of the 21st century in view. Its goal is to produce future leaders with knowledge and skills essential for leadership in country's private and public sector enterprises in the increasingly competitive and globalized environment. EU has been offering quality education in a good number of disciplines, including science and engineering, business, law, humanities. Now there is a pressing need and demand for enhancing on journalism and media.   
</p><br />
<p style="text-align:left;font-size:20px;font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;">Certificate Course on Print & Broadcast Journalism:</p>
<p>At the dawn of the 21st Century, the emergence of a number of satellite televisions channels in Bangladesh has forged a silent revolution in the field of electronic media. Along with the government-regulated BTV, Samsad TV, BTV World and Bangladesh Betar, Private TV Channels like ATN Bangla, ATN News, Banglavision, Bijoy TV, Boishakhi TV, Channel 16, Channel 24, Channel 9, Channel i, Deepto TV, Desh TV, Ekattor TV, Ekushey Television (ETV), Gaan Bangla, Gazi Television, Independent TV, Jamuna Television, Maasranga Television, Mohona TV, My TV, NTV, RTV, SA TV and Somoy Television have been acclaimed for news broadcast, talk shows and other popular programs.
</p>
<p>Meanwhile FM radios such as Radio Today, Radio Foorti, Radio Amar, Radio ABC, Radio Dhoni and Radio Shadhin are operating with great zeal. Besides, within a short span of time, Dhaka Bangla, Nagorik, News 24 and many others are about to join the market, making media booming for investment and employment. 
</p>
<p>Therefore, owing to the presence of these various television and FM radio channels journalism offers a very attractive and popular career at present. However, this attractive career in media requires proper orientation and training to become professionals. On the onset, in order to provide training to the budding journalists of the country, Office of the Public Relations of EU has designed an attractive, comprehensive and needs-based Certificate Course on Print & Broadcast Journalism.
</p><br />
<p style="text-align:left;font-size:20px;font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;">Aims & Objectives of the Course: </p>
<p>
At the moment, journalism is a sophisticated profession in the global arena. Young people are now interested and ready to work in the field to take the challenge. To equip these people with the appropriate orientation and required training, Eastern University offers a highly professional short course on Journalism. We promise to make the aspiring journalists become a professional journalist by the short coursed. We have designed the course taking the knowledge and the valuable experience of the experts and knowledgeable journalists and academic professionals into consideration. The target of the course is equipping the individuals with the practical knowledge and expertise who have short time to invest for learning journalism. Essentially, we aim to offer them the training and knowledge of full journalism background. The objectives are:
</p>
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;•&nbsp;&nbsp;Confer the students with the concepts of Journalism.
<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;•&nbsp;&nbsp;Make the students capable about print media (newspaper), television and online journalism.
<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;•&nbsp;&nbsp;Present a clear idea about news gathering, writing, editing, and publishing.
<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;•&nbsp;&nbsp;Bestow the students a clear concept about the political economy of Journalism in Bangladesh.
<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;•&nbsp;&nbsp;Make them capable to do modern journalism like citizen journalism, online-offline journalism, investigation reporting.
<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;•&nbsp;&nbsp;Make them familiar with television Journalism practically.

<p style="text-align:left;font-size:20px;font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;">Course Benefits:</p>
<p>AC classroom, autocue camera, multimedia and audio-visual instruments; practice session, voice recording and evaluation and free-hand practical; famous and experienced instructors; course materials and refreshments provided; job application techniques and opportunities to meet those already in the business; modern syllabus; certificates awarded for successful completion. 
</p>
<p style="text-align:left;font-size:20px;font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;">Course duration and details:</p>
<p>Two months’ course duration, including theory and practical classes; two days of classes per week (from 3pm to 5pm); class tests and examination. </p>

<p style="text-align:left;font-size:20px;font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;">Teaching Method </p>
<p>Theoretical Classed, Practical Classes, News Writing, Scripting, News Production, Presentation with Electronics Instrument of Television and Print Media. 
    </p>
