<p style="text-align:left;font-size:20px;font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;">Resource Persons </p>
<p>Eastern University Short Course on Journalism is operated by skilled and experienced personalities with higher academic degrees from home and abroad. They include eminent personalities and professionals from both the print and electronic media (journalists, news presenters, cameramen, video editors, photo journalists and so on), prominent faculty members of journalism and social science from various public and private university, ICT-experts and pronunciation experts etc. The curriculum has been designed in accordance with the international standards with the guidance of concerned experts. Practical activities are given equal importance alongside the theories.
</p><br />
<p style="text-align:left;font-size:20px;font-weight: bold; font-style: normal;">Admission Requirement, procedure & Fee:</p>
<p>Admission is open to any one who has completed or is about to complete HSC and above. Interested students should obtain and complete an admission form from EU’s Information Office for TK. 100/- (one hundred taka only). The total course fee is 5,000/- (Five thousand only) for the students of EU and 10,000/- (ten thousand taka only) for others.
